    MainActivity
    public class MainActivity.GetWeaponList
extends android.os.AsyncTask<java.lang.String,​java.lang.Void,​java.util.ArrayList<Weapon>>
    This searches for the weapons after the end user has clicked the search button.

    For 'extends AsyncTask'. the three types used by an asynchronous task are the following:

    • The params, the type of the parameters sent to the task upon execution. This is the end user's searched term as a string.
    • The progress, the type of the progress units published during the background computation. This is void.
    • The result, the type of the result of the background computation. This is an array weaponArrayList of weapons.

    22.3

      • doInBackground

        protected java.util.ArrayList<Weapon> doInBackground​(java.lang.String... params)
        This searches for weapons in the background.

        doInBackground is invoked on the background thread immediately after onPreExecute() finishes executing. This is used to perform background computation that can take a long time, such as retrieving the weapon screenshot, icons, statistics, and perks. The parameters of the asynchronous task are passed to this step. The result of the computation must be returned by this step and will be passed back to the last step.

        Specified by:
